---
import ExperienceCard from "../components/ExperienceCard.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Rendani Gangazhe - Software Engineer">
  <h1>About me</h1>

  <p class="text-lg mt-8">
    I'm Rendani Gangazhe, a full stack web/mobile app developer and Computer
    Science student based in Freiburg, Germany. Orignally from South Africa, I
    moved here to study and experience a new culture and learn a new language. I
    like keeping a wide range of interests besides coding and enjoy training and
    playing guitar &#127928; The name "Rendani" is a
    <a
      class="font-bold underline"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venda_people"
      target="_blank"
    >
      <strong>Tshivenda</strong>
    </a> unisex name meaning "praise/give praise" and is under no circumstances
    <a
      class="font-bold underline"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendani_Airport"
      target="_blank"
    >
      <strong>to be confused with the airport.</strong>
    </a>
  </p>

  <div class="mt-16 h-1" id="experience"/>

  <article>
    <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

    <ExperienceCard
      title="Mäuschen App"
      href="https://mäuschen.app/"
      from="2020"
      to="2022"
      body="Responsible for building cross-platform mobile apps using Flutter Built out JSON APIs using Express.js, containerised them with Docker/Docker-componse and deployed them in Kubernetes clusters. "
    />
  </article>

  <div class="mt-16 h-1" id="skills"/>

  <article class="flex flex-col gap-4">
    <h2>Technical Skills</h2>

    <section>
      <p class="text-lg">
        I'm most experienced using <strong>JavaScript</strong> and <strong
          >TypeScript</strong
        > for both front and backend development and am also comfortable using
        <strong>Dart</strong> along with the <strong>Flutter</strong> UI kit for
        cross-platform mobile app development.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-4 mt-4">
      <section class="p-4 bg-zinc-800">
        <h3 class="text-xl">Frontend</h3>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          Regarding <strong>Flutter</strong> app development, I have professional
          experience with various state management libraries including <strong
            >Provider</strong
          >
          and <strong>Riverpod</strong>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          On the web development side of things, I build user interfaces with
          pure <strong>HTML5/CSS3</strong> and larger more interactive web apps using
          <strong>Svelte</strong>
          and <strong>Sveltekit</strong>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          I also have some knowledge of <strong>React</strong> and
          <strong>Next.js</strong>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="p-4 bg-zinc-800">
        <h3 class="text-xl">Backend</h3>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          On the backend I'm most experienced with <strong>Node.js</strong> and use
          it build out with <strong>Express.js</strong> APIs.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          My preferred database is <strong>Firebase</strong> but I also have experience
          using <strong>MinIO</strong>, <strong>MySQL</strong> and other similar
          relational databases following the SQL standard.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-4">
      <section class="p-4 bg-zinc-800">
        <h3 class="text-xl">Other languages and tools</h3>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          I've used <strong>Python</strong> and <strong>Go</strong> but haven't used
          them in any professional settings.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          I'm also familiar the usual developer tools such as <strong
            >Git</strong
          >, <strong>Gitea</strong>, <strong>Github</strong> and
          <strong>Jira</strong>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="p-4 bg-zinc-800">
        <h3 class="text-xl">DevOps</h3>

        <p class="text-lg mt-4">
          I leverage <strong>Docker</strong> and <strong>Kubernetes</strong> to help
          build containerised web services deployed through <strong
            >CI-CD</strong
          > pipelines
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  section {
    flex: 1;
  }
</style>
